snippet: In another brutal matchup between rivals, Michael Del Zotto’s goal for the Rangers at 1:33 of the third period — 36 seconds after Wayne Simmonds tied the score — turned out to be the winner.
abstract: New York Rangers defeat Philadelphia Flyers, 5-2, in NHL action.
lead_paragraph: In another brutal matchup between rivals, Michael Del Zotto’s goal for the Rangers at 1:33 of the third period — 36 seconds after Wayne Simmonds tied the score — turned out to be the winner.

headline.seo: Rangers’ Mastery of Flyers Continues in Latest Testy Matchup
headline.main: Rangers’ Mastery in a Testy Rivalry Continues
